<subsection xml:id="subsec-c">
    <title>Speed </title>
    <p>
        <m>\textbf{Speed}</m> is the rate of change of distance with time. SI unit: <m>km/h</m> .
    </p>
    <p>
        Speed normally varies over time, so the average speed is often used
    </p>
    <p>
        <md>
            <mrow>\textbf{Average speed} = \frac{\textbf{Total distance covered}}{\textbf{Total time taken}} </mrow>
        </md>
    </p>
    <activity>
        <p>
            <m>{\color{black} \textbf{Work in groups}}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>\textbf{Materials}</m>; Stop watch, Measuring tape and ball/round object 
        </p>
        <p>
            Roll a ball or any round object on the table 
        </p>
        <p>
            Measure the rolling distance using the tape measure
        </p>
        <p>
            Record the time when rolling
        </p>
        <p>
            Find the speed of the rolling ball
        </p>
    </activity>
    <activity>
        <p>
            <m>{\color{black} \textbf{Work in groups}}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            A family drives 120 km at 60 km/h, stops for a 15-minute break, and then drives another 80 km at 40 km/h. 
            What is the average speed for the entire trip?
        </p>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Calculate the time for each driving segment
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Convert the break time to hours
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Calculate the total distance
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Calculate the total time
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Calculate the average speed
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </activity>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                A car travels 100 km in 2 hours. Find its speed.
            </p>
        </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    <m>\textbf{Speed} = \frac{\textbf{distance}}{\textbf{time}}</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <m> \textbf{Speed} = \frac{100}{2} = 50 \text{ km/h} </m>
                </p>
                
            </solution>
    </example>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                A motorist covers a distance of 360 km in 3 hours travelling from busia to bahangongo. Calculate the average speed.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                <m>\textbf{Speed} = \frac{\textbf{distance}}{\textbf{time}}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> \textbf{Average speed} = \frac{\textbf{360 km}}{\textbf{3 h}} </mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> \textbf{120 km/h} </mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Alex is cycling from home to the market. He rides the first 8 km at a speed of 16 km/h. After reaching a park, 
                Alex takes a 20-minute break to play football with his friends. Then, he cycles the remaining 6 km to the market at a speed of 12 km/h.
                What was Alex's average speed for the entire journey?
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Calculating the time for each cycling part.
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        <m>\textbf{part 1}</m>
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        Distance: <m>\textbf{8 km}</m>
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        Speed: <m>\textbf{16 km/h}</m>
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        <md>
                                            <mrow>\textbf{Time}\, = \, \frac{Distance}{Speed} \, = \, \frac{\textbf{8 km}}{16 km/h} \,  = \textbf{0.5 hours}</mrow>
                                        </md>
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        <m>\textbf{part 2}</m>
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        Distance: <m>\textbf{6 km}</m>
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        Speed: <m>\textbf{12 km/h}</m>
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        <md>
                                            <mrow>\textbf{Time}\, = \, \frac{Distance}{Speed} \, = \, \frac{\textbf{6 km}}{12 km/h} \,  = \textbf{0.5 hours}</mrow>
                                        </md>
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Convert the break time to hours
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>\frac{\textbf{20 minutes}}{\textbf{60 minutes}} = \frac{1}{3} \, hours</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Calculating the total distance gives
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <md>
                                <mrow> \textbf {Total distance = 8 km + 6 km = 14 km }</mrow>
                            </md>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Calculating the total time gives
                        </p>
                        <p> Total time =
                            <md>
                                <mrow> \frac{1}{2} \, hours + \frac{1}{3} \, hours + \frac{1}{2} \, hours = 1\frac{1}{3} \, hours  </mrow>
                            </md>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Now Calculating the average speed gives
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>\textbf{Average speed} \, = \, \frac{\textbf{Total distance}}{\textbf{Total time}}</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>\textbf{Average speed} \, = \, \frac{\textbf{14 km}}{\textbf{1.33 hours}} \, = \, \textbf{10.53 km/h} </m> 
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
            <p>
                Alex's average speed for the entire journey was approximately <m>\textbf{10.53 km/h} </m>.
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    
    <exercises xml:id="exercises-linear-motion-speed">
